Yes, my understanding is the [server](https://serverfault.com/questions/801628/for-server-sent-events-sse-what-nginx-proxy-configuration-is-appropriate) should set that header automatically if the content-length is unknown. Only the headers:

```
Content-Type: text/event-stream;
Cache-Control: no-cache;
X-Accel-Buffering: no;
```

[should be necessary](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Server-sent_events/Using_server-sent_events)

